</taxonomicName>
R.Br.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="090FD8CC46F5C32F068D437527CD9C14" pageId="1" pageNumber="102" type="notes">
<paragraph id="741F9C991208619EB5E26E649CBF3C24" pageId="1" pageNumber="102">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D76561B595AECB327C7C4DA1B4DC87AF" pageId="1" pageNumber="102">
When they resurrected 
<taxonomicName id="B65B8546AD5A2AF17E9AABC6EFB2DA29" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Heliotropiaceae" genus="Euploca" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Euploca" order="Boraginales" pageId="1" pageNumber="102" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="AF8D1D1863A7989C44674345EC0B41F3" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="102">Euploca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="FB3FAB0544E7C053EF5EDB0B2CD70238" author="Hilger, HH" journalOrPublisher="Botanische Jahrbuecher fuer Systematik Pflanzengeschichte und Pflanzengeographie" pageId="11" pageNumber="112" pagination="19 - 51" publicationUrl="http://www.ingentaconnect.com/content/schweiz/bj/2003/00000125/00000001/art00002" refId="B23" refString="Hilger, HH, Diane, N, 2003. A systematic analysis of Heliotropiaceae (Boraginales) based on trnL and ITS1 sequence data. Botanische Jahrbuecher fuer Systematik Pflanzengeschichte und Pflanzengeographie 125 (1): 19 - 51, http://www.ingentaconnect.com/content/schweiz/bj/2003/00000125/00000001/art00002" title="A systematic analysis of Heliotropiaceae (Boraginales) based on trnL and ITS 1 sequence data." url="http://www.ingentaconnect.com/content/schweiz/bj/2003/00000125/00000001/art00002" volume="125" year="2003">Hilger and Diane (2003</bibRefCitation>
: 42) said that &quot;summarizing all urges a formal taxonomic recombination of EUPLOCA, including all species of 
<taxonomicName id="C47201CC1048E6358203C3F965326E59" authority="Orthostachys" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Heliotropiaceae" genus="Heliotropium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Heliotropium subsp. section" order="Boraginales" pageId="1" pageNumber="102" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="section" section="Orthostachys" species="foliatum" subSpecies="section">Heliotropium section Orthostachys</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="19A5F78D77205BBB700E620E0FFEBEE5" authority="Endl." authorityName="Endl." class="Magnoliopsida" family="Heliotropiaceae" genus="Schleidenia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Schleidenia" order="Boraginales" pageId="1" pageNumber="102" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="D694AA76F90F916A1B5D5D1B25EC65A8" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="102">Schleidenia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="C0EE3CCC3D8C92C32FDA44572AA246B6" authority="Foerther, 1998" authorityName="Foerther" authorityYear="1998" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Heliotropiaceae" genus="Hilgeria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Hilgeria" order="Boraginales" pageId="1" pageNumber="102" phylum="Streptophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B6A9BD87E792AB6A8B67D6235FBEC564" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="102">Hilgeria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
into the genus 
<taxonomicName id="6AA4F68C6D054A585552EC70CD98C9F5" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Heliotropiaceae" genus="Euploca" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Euploca" order="Boraginales" pageId="1" pageNumber="102" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="9549AE2529B065B59CF5A94C5FE321B4" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="102">Euploca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the oldest available generic name in this group.&quot; 
<taxonomicName id="A3F913E9D9BCF9500D2131F7A1E89EE0" authorityName="Feuillet" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Feuillet" baseAuthorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Heliotropiaceae" genus="Heliotropium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Heliotropium foliatum" order="Boraginales" pageId="1" pageNumber="102" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="foliatum">
<emphasis id="7CA50AB11471511FB4A82EB1FEAE8CF4" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="102">Heliotropium foliatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the type of 
<taxonomicName id="1EBD05694DA30F07FEC454051CC5E802" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Heliotropiaceae" genus="Heliotropium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Heliotropium subsp. sect." order="Boraginales" pageId="1" pageNumber="102" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="section" section="Orthostachys" species="foliatum" subSpecies="sect.">Heliotropium sect. Orthostachys</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="CF7A455615A29DC275CF692009DE224E" author="Johnston, IM" journalOrPublisher="Contributions from the Gray Herbarium" pageId="11" pageNumber="112" pagination="3 - 73" publicationUrl="http://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/item/122400page/1/mode/1up" refId="B26" refString="Johnston, IM, 1928. Studies in the Boraginaceae VII. The South American Species of Heliotropium. Contributions from the Gray Herbarium 81: 3 - 73, http://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/item/122400page/1/mode/1up" title="Studies in the Boraginaceae VII. The South American Species of Heliotropium." url="http://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/item/122400page/1/mode/1up" volume="81" year="1928">Johnston 1928</bibRefCitation>
: 46). Although it is recognized as a good species (example: 
<bibRefCitation id="2BE9E5BC0A123809013CAE13F14DD9C9" author="Foerther, H" journalOrPublisher="Sendtnera" pageId="10" pageNumber="111" pagination="35 - 241" publicationUrl="http://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/item/52056page/1/mode/2up" refId="B15" refString="Foerther, H, 1998. Die infragenerische Gliederung der Gattung Heliotropium L. und ihre Stellung innerhalb der subfam. Heliotropioidea (Schrad.) Arn. (Boraginaceae). Sendtnera 5: 35 - 241, http://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/item/52056page/1/mode/2up" title="Die infragenerische Gliederung der Gattung Heliotropium L. und ihre Stellung innerhalb der subfam. Heliotropioidea (Schrad.) Arn. (Boraginaceae)." url="http://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/item/52056page/1/mode/2up" volume="5" year="1998">
<normalizedToken id="9AB9B874516B14D0D8B13DE75BFDF583" originalValue="Förther">Foerther</normalizedToken>
1998
</bibRefCitation>
: 195), 
<taxonomicName id="28D0A1B82ADF5F7479923BBB4AB6258C" authorityName="Feuillet" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Feuillet" baseAuthorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Heliotropiaceae" genus="Heliotropium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Heliotropium foliatum" order="Boraginales" pageId="1" pageNumber="102" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="foliatum">
<emphasis id="AD04F42808018B2270DEF415C3CF423D" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="102">Heliotropium foliatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was not transferred to 
<taxonomicName id="195FF5C12663C6AD88A78248049C70E7" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Heliotropiaceae" genus="Euploca" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Euploca" order="Boraginales" pageId="1" pageNumber="102" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="CC25AD3C49779EFEBB03168BF72B8B5F" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="102">Euploca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
until now. Robert Brown did not cite a type collection, only mentioning &quot;v. v.&quot; (=seen alive).
</paragraph>
